{
	"mim_type": "announcement",
	"rule_name": "",
	"timeout": 6,
	"barge_in": true,
	"es_auto_tagging": false,
	"notes": "Turn off embodied speech.",
	"prompts": [
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-1\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. Something didn't go as I'd planned. Be sure to look directly at my screen while I do this. <break size='0.3'/> Starting again, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_01",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-0\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I'm not seeing anyone in front of me. It could be the light is bad, or you're too far away, or you're moving. Make sure you're in the frame, about an arm's length away from me.  <break size='0.3'/>Here we go.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_02",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-2\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I see two faces in front of me, and for now it should be only ${loopMember}. If I'm wrong, you may want to move me just a little, because sometimes I think things like windows and plants are faces. Pretty embarrassing. <break size='0.3'/> Okay let's try again.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_03",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-3\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. For some reason, I see three faces right now. If there are not three people, maybe re-orient me just a little, because I sometimes think windows and plants are faces. Because I'm a robot. <break size='0.3'/> We can pick up where we left off, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_04",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-4\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I'm seeing four faces in front of me. If I'm wrong, and there aren't four of you, you may want to move my direction just a little. Sometimes I see faces in things like windows and plants. I know it's spooky. <break size='0.3'/> Starting again, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_05",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-5\"",
			"prompt": "I'm seeing five people for some reason. If I'm mistaken and there aren't a bunch of people standing there, you may want to move my direction just a little, because very rarely, I confuse things like windows and plants for faces. It's a little embarrassing. <break size='0.3'/> Okay, let me pick up where we left off. Studying your face, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_06",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-many\"",
			"prompt": "I'm seeing a lot of people for some reason. If I'm mistaken and there aren't a bunch of people standing there, you may want to move my direction just a little, because every once in a while, I confuse things like windows and plants for faces. It's a little embarrassing. <break size='0.3'/> Okay, let me pick up where we left off. Studying your face, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_07",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-1\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. Well that didn't work for some reason. Make sure you're looking directly at my screen, and I will try again.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_08",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-1\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. That didn't quite work. I'll try again, look right at my screen.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_09",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-0\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I don't see anyone right now. It could be the light, or you're moving, or maybe you are far away from me. Just make sure you can see yourself in the viewfinder. <break size='0.3'/> And I'll try again now.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_10",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-0\" && Math.random()<.5",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I can't see anyone at the moment. Maybe it's not enough light, or you're far away, or you're moving, or you turned into a ghost. Position yourself using my viewfinder, and I'll try again now.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_11",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-2\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I'm seeing two faces right now. This works much better if only ${loopMember} is in front of me. If I'm wrong and there aren't two people, maybe try moving me a little bit, because I might be seeing faces where there aren't any. <break size='0.3'/> Alright, let's try again.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_12",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-2\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I'm seeing two faces, and I'd really like to just look at ${loopMember}. <break size='0.3'/> I'll try again in a sec.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_13",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-3\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I see three faces, and I really want to just see ${loopMember}. If I'm seeing imaginary people, maybe try moving my direction a little bit. Sometimes I see faces in inanimate objects. Pretty spooky, I know. <break size='0.3'/> Anyway, I'll try again, in three, two, one.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_14",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-3\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. It seems like there are three faces here, and it'd be much better to see only ${loopMember}. <break size='0.3'/> I'll try again now.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_15",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-4\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. It could be my mistake, but I see four faces right now. I would love to see only ${loopMember}. <break size='0.3'/> I'll give it another shot.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_16",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-4\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I see four faces right now. If I'm mistaken, maybe move me a bit. It's possible I'm seeing imaginary faces. <break size='0.3'/> Let's try it again.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_17",
			"weight": 1
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-5\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. It could be my mistake, but I see five faces right now. I would love to see only ${loopMember}. <break size='0.3'/> I'll give it another shot.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_18",
			"weight": 1,
			"auto_rule_override": null
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-5\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I see five faces right now. If I'm mistaken, maybe move me a bit. It's possible I'm seeing imaginary faces. <break size='0.3'/> Let's try it again.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_19",
			"weight": 1,
			"auto_rule_override": null
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-many\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. It could be my mistake, but I see a lot of faces right now. I would love to see only ${loopMember}. <break size='0.3'/> I'll give it another shot.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_20",
			"weight": 1,
			"auto_rule_override": null
		},
		{
			"prompt_category": "Entry-Core",
			"prompt_sub_category": "AN",
			"index": 1,
			"condition": "errorType===\"detect-many\"",
			"prompt": "<ssa cat='oops'/>. I see a lot of faces right now. If I'm mistaken, maybe move me a bit. It's possible I'm seeing imaginary faces. <break size='0.3'/> Let's try it again.",
			"media": "TTS",
			"prompt_id": "FaceCapture_Error2_AN_21",
			"weight": 1,
			"auto_rule_override": null
		}
	],
	"gui": null,
	"no_matches_for_gui": 2,
	"no_inputs_for_gui": 2,
	"ignore_no_match": false,
	"parse_all_asr": false,
	"thanks_handling": "ignore",
	"parse_launch": false
}